staticgmap
==========

staticgmap is a lightweight tool to create static Google maps.

More information and examples: http://tools.s2studio.co.uk/staticgmap/

License: http://tools.s2studio.co.uk/staticgmap/#license

Copyright (c) 2012 Sarunas Savicianskas - sarunas@s2studio.co.uk


How to use
----------

To get started, download the plugin, unzip it and copy files to your website/application directory.
Load files in the <head> section of your HTML document. Make sure you also add the jQuery library.

    <head>
        <script type="text/javascript" src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7/jquery.min.js"></script>
        <script type="text/javascript" src="/staticgmap/jquery.staticgmap.1.0.1.js"></script>
    </head>

Create a html element, and add an id:

    <div id="element">This is where the static Google map should be generated by jQuery plugin!</div>

Initialise the script like this:

    <script>
        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('#element').staticgmap();
        });
    </script>

May also be passed an optional options object which will extend the default values. Example:

    <script>
        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('#element').staticgmap({
                address : '39 Steventon Road, London, UK',
                width   : 400,
                height  : 300
            });
        });
    </script>

Advanced
--------

You can customise the staticgmap as much as you want by passing specific options. Example:

    $("#element").staticgmap({
        width   : 300,
        height  : 250,
        zoom    : 14,
        maptype : 'hybrid', // roadmap, satellite, terrain, hybrid
        address : 'Tower Bridge, United Kingdom', // address or coordinates
        atlText : 'This is a static Google map generated by jQuery'
    });

### API

It`s possible to update staticgmap programmatically:

    $("#element").staticgmap('update', {
        width   : 600,
        height  : 400,
        zoom    : 17,
        maptype : 'satellite', // roadmap, satellite, terrain, hybrid
        address : 'Tower Bridge, United Kingdom', // address or coordinates
        atlText : 'This is an updated static Google map generated by jQuery'
    });

There are several methods that allow you to interact with and manipulate staticgmap, example:

    // Destroy staticgmap:
    $("#element").staticgmap('destroy');


Bug tracker
-----------

Have a bug? Please create an issue on GitHub at https://github.com/s2sarunas/staticgmap/issues